> This Speedy Sausage and Bacon Rigatoni is a crowd pleaser and is one to get the
> family round the dinner table for. Super simple to make, and easily
> customised to suit the kids too.

== Prepare ==

Fill and boil your #kettle{}.

Heat a drizzle of oil in a #large frying pan{} on medium-high heat.

Once hot, add the @British smoked bacon lardons{90%g} and @British pork and
oregano sausage meat{225%g}, fry until browned, ~{5-6%minutes}. Use a #spoon{}
to break up the sausage meat as it cooks.

> IMPORTANT: Wash your hands and equipment after handling raw meat. Sausages
> are cooked when no longer pink in the middle. Cook bacon thoroughly.

Fill a #large saucepan{} on high heat with the boiling water and add
@salt{1/2%tsp}.

Add the @rigatoni pasta{180%g} and bring back to the boil. Cook until tender,
~{12%minutes}.

Once cooked, drain in a #colander{} and pop back into the pan. Drizzle with
oil and stir through to stop it sticking together.

== Make the Sauce ==

Once the sausage meat and lardons have browned, drain and discard any excess
fat.

Add the @balsamic vinegar{12%ml} and allow it to evaporate for ~{30%seconds}.

Stir in the @sun-dried tomato paste{25%g} and cook for ~{1%minute}.

== Simmer the Sauce ==

Add the @finely chopped tomatoes with basil{1%can}, @chicken stock paste{10%g},
@sugar{1} and @water{50%ml} to the sausage meat.

Stir and bring to the boil, then lower the heat.

Simmer until thickened, ~{5-6%minutes}.

== Finish ==

Once the sauce has thickened, stir through the @baby spinach{100%g} a handful
at a time until wilted and piping hot, ~{2-3%minutes}.

Season to taste with @salt{} and @pepper{} if needed.

Add the cooked rigatoni to the sausage sauce, along with the
@hard Italian style cheese{20%g}(grated).

Toss together until combined.

Serve your sausage rigatoni in #bowls{} and dig in.

Enjoy!